{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbe38b3e-8415-430f-91ff-472d8a4e5d1d","content":"Yes, both approaches are correct for .NET MAUI on .NET 10:\n\n**1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Correct. Add the namespace and the property:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\nThis insets your page content to avoid the notch/Dynamic Island and home indicator.\n\n**2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — Also correct. When `UseSafeArea` is enabled on the page, individual views can opt out to extend edge-to-edge (e.g., for a background image):\n\n```xml\n<Grid IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\">\n    <Image Source=\"background.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</Grid>\n```\n\nThis is the standard pattern: enable safe area at the page level, then selectively ignore it on elements that should bleed to the edges.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f767a87-3c78-4a66-a5f8-5d6e197fb9d7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` on a ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid for a background image\n\nThey want to know if these are correct for .NET 10. Let me search for information about this in the current repository, as it seems to contain .NET MAUI related plugins/skills. But actually, this might be a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI APIs.\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n\n1. **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** - This is a platform-specific property from `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific`. \n\nFor the iOS safe area property, I need to use the platform-specific namespace and set it on the page to respect safe area boundaries. The `IgnoreSafeArea` property on a Grid would allow content to extend into the safe area, which is useful when you want a 